            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-08-26 10:34:26" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to take by force or stealth objects from a temple</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to rob temples</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It is also possible to interpret ἱεροσυλέω in {S:04500202200020} as meaning ‘to commit sacrilege,’ in the sense of doing harm or damage to sacred objects in temples (see {D:53.104}).</Comments>
